##
## Fonctionnement
##
@node functions "How it works"

Very easy ! (in a way....)

CareTime "MESSAGE/K,EVERY/K/A,PUBSCREEN/K,POSX/K,POSY/K,TITLE/K,CLOCK/S,
EXECUTE/K,LOGFILE/K/,HOTKEY/K,NOLOG/S"

CareTime is a commodity now. The window could be HIDE or not
CareTime will produce a logfile (like NComm in order to be compatible with
PhoneCall). When you launch CareTime it will start the log file, if you
launch it again it will stop the logfile (so you can add a line to start
CareTime in startnet, and add a line in stopnet)
If your machine crashs while you were connected CareTime will ask you the
next time if the modem is still on line (and it will continue like if your
amiga had not crashed (hope you understand me :-). If you have shut off your
modem it will ask you how -minutes- you were on line to complete the logfile


@{"  Message   " link message}
@{"  Every     " link every}
@{"  PubScreen " link pubscreen}
@{"  PosX      " link pos}
@{"  PosY      " link pos}
@{"  Title     " link title}
@{"  Clock     " link clock}
@{"  Execute   " link Execute}
@{"  LogFile   " link LogFile}
@{"  HotKey    " link Hotkey}
@{"  NoLog     " link NoLog}
@{"  Keys      " link key}


CareTime can be launch from the workbench so every option could be passed
by the icon; tooltypes are:
  PUBSCREEN=
  CLOCK
  POSX=
  POSY=
  TITLE=
  MESSAGE=
  EVERY=
  EXECUTE=
  LOGFILE=
  HOTKEY=
  NOLOG

IMPORTANT: you MUST quote the tooltype (passed by Workbench or CLI) is
~~~~~~~~~  there is more than 2 words
           eg: MESSAGE="Yoh Dude"  or  TITLE="Time Online"


@endnode

##
## Installation
##
@node install Install

CareTime need OS 2.0 at least and the Reqtools.library ((c) Nico
Francois)
It will work with the CLI and with Workbench.
To install you can:
  Copy CareTime where you like,and do the same with its documen-
  tation.  if you have a 68020 machine it will be better to copy
  CareTime020. Copy the reqtools.library to the drawer Libs:

  Or You can drag the icon where you like to install CareTime.

@endnode


@node every "Every"

every is the number of minutes to wait before the requester
appears.
Note: more than 1 minute please, or it will crash
every MUST be supply

eg: CareTime EVERY 15 MESSAGE "Hey ! you has been connecte for"

in 90 (=15*6) minutes the result will be:
    ----------------------------------
    |Hey ! you has been connected for|
    |             01:30              |
    ----------------------------------
    |              |Ok|              |
    ----------------------------------

@endnode


@node message "Message"

message  is what will appear in the requester every minutes. The last line
will give you from how many time CareTime is lauch.

eg: CareTime EVERY 10 MESSAGE "hey ! you has been connected for"

    ----------------------------------
    |Hey ! you has been connected for|
    |             01:30              |
    ----------------------------------
    |              |Ok|              |
    ----------------------------------

Note: if you don't want a requester don't supply a message. (if you want
only the logfile)

@endnode

@node pubscreen "PubScreen"

you could give a pubscreen if you want.

eg: CareTime EVERY 15 PUBSCREEN myscreen

@endnode

@node pos "posX posY"

you can give x,y postion  for the caretime's window.

eg: CareTime EVERY 10 POSX 10 POSY 200

so the window will open its top left border at 10,200

@endnode

@node title "title"

title is the title (!) that will be printed in the logfile

eg: Caretime EVERY 10 TITLE="InterNet from my home (00)"

NB: you must give a title like this: "blahblah (xx)"
where xx is a number                           ~~~~
this number is the phone of your provider     !IMPORTANT!

so the log file will be like this:

InterNet from my home (00)
--------------------------------
Login:  Sat Feb 10 19:28:55 1996
Logout: Sat Feb 10 19:29:00 1996
Time online: 00:00:05

InterNet from my home (00)
--------------------------------
Login:  Sat Feb 10 19:29:15 1996
Logout: Sat Feb 10 19:49:15 1996
Time online: 00:00:20

.
.
.

the default title is "Internet (00)"

@endnode

@node clock "Clock"

if you ask for clock CareTime will start will in its window and not
with chrono. You can switch between clock/chrono with TAB key

eg: CareTime EVERY 10 CLOCK

@endnode

@node execute "Execute"

CareTime could execute a command (CLI) but be careful ! CareTime does not
take care of it, if there is an error or something like this CareTime can
do ... nothing
The command will be execute just before the requester 'll appear and with
every requesters of course

eg: CareTime EVERY 10 MESSAGE "Hey !" EXECUTE "play st-00:warning"

caretime will play warning (i suppose that it is a sample) with every
requester

Note: if you do not supply a message CareTime will only execute the
"play st-00:warning"

@endnode


@node logfile "Log File"

logfile is the name of your logfile; by default it is: "progdir:caretime.log"

eg: CareTime EVERY 10 LOGFILE work:logfile_of_caretime

@endnode


@node key "Keys"

CareTime will open a window. You will be able to switch between
clock and time by pressing TAB. Time can be reset by pressing 0

@endnode

@node Hotkey "HotKey"

The hotkey is not very useful, in fact you can show/hide the window of caretime
by default it is "alt r", but you can change it.. If your choice is not good it
will return you an error.

@endnode

@node NoLog "NoLog"

If this flag is active, the logfile will not be actived

@endnode


